            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My experience with NNPS Kolkata has revealed significant administrative and operational failures. Parents should be aware of the following before going to admission:\n\n        Affiliation Transparency: Despite two years of assurances, there is no verified CBSE affiliation, and updates regarding the new campus remain vague and inconsistent.\n\n        Academic Standards: The teaching staff demonstrates a lack of proficiency in the CBSE pedagogical framework. Academic oversight is poor, evidenced by the irregularity of PTMs.\n\n        Welfare Concerns: Management has implemented highly restrictive policies regarding basic student needs, including access to drinking water and toilets during school hours.\n\n        Operational Focus: The administration appears more invested in extracurricular \"performances\" for marketing purposes than in providing a robust academic foundation or adequate infrastructure.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
